19:
Calm down,
and tell me what happened.
31:
Alk, what is all the fuss about?
What is hatching?
43:
Stella found it. The little guy's been
going at it for a while, but...
its movements are getting weaker...
46:
We searched for its parents,
but we cannot find them.
We fear they may be... gone.
50:
We didn't know if it'd be okay to touch
the egg, which is why Stella went
and got you.
56:
I am sorry,
but there is nothing I can do.
61:
Huh? Why not?
Will we hurt the egg if we touch it?
66:
I do not know. Like you,
I have not the faintest idea what to do.
68: The Ancients do not lay eggs.
70: To us, death is just another beginning.
71:
We sleep, and we forget... But always,
in time, another dragon with the
same form and name will appear...
73: Thus, there are no babes among us.
75:
We are different from the dragons
of this world.
79:
Ah... But it seems there was no cause
for worry after all.
86: I-it hatched! No way! That's so cool!
95:
So this is how new lives come
into being...
97:
Heh. Perhaps there IS something I can
do for you, my distant brethren...
101:
I shall see that nothing clouds the day
of your birth.
109:
We should not have jumped
to conclusions.
112:
There is no need for apologies.
You showed me something wondrous.
114:
And it reminded me of something
from my past.
122:
I have never cared for an egg...
But I once cared for a human child.
124: Even though he had come to kill me.
128:
His eyes were full of hatred...
loathing towards dragons.
I had every right to take his life.
129:
But... I could not bring myself to do it.
I tended his woundshurts that I had
inflicted in self-defense.
138:
I hope he has found somewhere
he may live in contentment.
142: Don't you want to see him again?
146:
Haha. I do not wish for what
I cannot have, Alk.
150:
But IF we were to meet again,
I believe he would understand...
My vision for a world where mortal,
dragon, and fiend may dwell
together in peace.
